OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1773565532
OL,3,CRowers circumnavigating Britain in
OL,4,C'brutal' charity challenge arrive in
OL,5,CScotland
OL,7,FSpeaking to the Press Association, he
OL,8,Fsaid: "When it's two in the morning,
OL,9,Fin the pitch black, in the fog, with
OL,10,Fthe sea smashing the boat around, with
OL,11,Fyour oars going in different
OL,12,Fdirections, when you've been rowing
OL,13,Ffor seven days, two hours on, two
OL,14,Fhours off, and you're cold ` it's
OL,15,Fbrutal."
OL,17,FBut Mr Parker, originally from
OL,18,FKilmarnock but who now lives in
OL,19,FSurrey, said he has never doubted
OL,20,Fwhether the challenge is worth it.
OL,26,@pD@GOUwD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1773565532
OL,3,CRowers circumnavigating Britain in
OL,4,C'brutal' charity challenge arrive in
OL,5,CScotland
OL,7,F"It's the best thing I've ever done in
OL,8,Fmy life," he said.
OL,10,F"It's brutal but never miserable,
OL,11,Fnever unhappy.
OL,13,F"I'd be lying if I said you don't
OL,14,Fthink 'why on Earth am I doing this'
OL,15,Fevery so often.
OL,17,F"But you suddenly ask yourself that
OL,18,Fquestion, and then you think about it,
OL,19,Fand I know exactly why I'm doing this,
OL,20,Fand this is great. I'm so lucky that I
OL,21,Fget to do something like this."
OL,26,@oD@AOUpD@IO]rD@AOUuD@AOUyD@AOU}D@_O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
